summary:
. . grew up into life via acting in England . . in theatre fell into luck with Orson Welles as director 
with a weird and wonderful part in a weird and wonderful play with Orson Himself as the dreaded 
Captain Ahab . . which in turn got me inducted into the Old Vic Theatre doing Shakespeare with 
the magical Richard Burton  /John Neville . . and on - the - edge - of-tears and -delight Wendy Hiller
~ learned so much just being on stage with them. . with all of them . . a magical film role in Lewis 
Gilbert's 'Greengage Summer ' which discovered the delicious Susannah York .she growing up and moi playing a very naughty ( what else ? ) French pot-boy n the Hotel where Susannah and her very young  perfectly English sister  -played  by Jane Asher . . were ( because their Aunt was taken ill ) left very 
much to their own growing -up devices . . ah the joy of growing up in the game - the joy of acting . .m.m.m ~~ this must be enough for now . . have rambled on already too far . . too very much . . never
quite left this life of theatre . . of invention . .  became a television director for a while . . then commercials   and now using the groundwork of acting . . doing voice -over work. .
